of America  is typically one of the largest in the United States  That American Mathematics Competition 8 is taken by more than 100 000 students each year   It s one of the most prestigious mathematics competitions  said Maj  Randy Cone  assistant professor of mathematics  who organized the event   For us  it s become a way to connect with our K through 12 colleagues    We ve turned the AMC into something more than a competition at VMI    We come together  and we have some fun with math  On Tuesday morning  students arriving for the test and afternoon program were greeted by drummers from the VMI Regimental Band  While the students were taking the 40 minute test  Lt  Col  Meagan Herald  associate professor of applied mathematics  gave a workshop for their teachers  administrators  and chaperones on active and inquiry based learning in mathematics  After a boxed lunch  AMC8 participants listened to talks about mathematics given by Col  Troy Siemers  head of the Department of Applied Mathematics at VMI  and Dr  Dan Joseph of Liberty University  Before heading home  many students and teachers took cadet led tours of the VMI post  In addition to endeavoring to create excitement about math for students  this year the AMC8 VMI emphasized giving back to the community as well  Participating AMC8 schools and teachers brought with them approximately 100 books suitable for students in grades kindergarten through five  to be distributed to those in need through the Rockbridge Reads program  Also  because one school cancelled at the last minute due to cold temperatures  and some students and teachers chose not to eat the boxed lunches provided  there were approximately 75 lunches left over on Tuesday  These were donated to the Campus Kitchen at neighboring Washington and Lee University  which distributed them to communities in need in Rockbridge County  Student participants received mechanical pencils as gifts  courtesy of the Society of Industrial and Applied Mathematics  SIAM  Their teachers also received math related gifts from the SIAM  including 30 math modeling textbooks    Mary Price    VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 